How to use the KNN sleepwalk wrapper

This code tests the wrapper function for a KNN-based sleepwalk.

source('../src/knn_sleepwalk.R')
library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(flowCore)
library(sleepwalk)
set.seed(1)

setwd(here::here('data'))
Warning: The working directory was changed to /Users/tylerburns/Documents/projects/knn_sleepwalk/data inside a notebook chunk. The working directory will be reset when the chunk is finished running. Use the knitr root.dir option in the setup chunk to change the working directory for notebook chunks.
# Read in the cells
cells <- flowCore::read.FCS(list.files(pattern = "SLE")) # Data from Marie Burns
params <- as.vector(Biobase::pData(parameters(cells))$desc)
colnames(cells) <- params
cells <- exprs(cells) 
cells <- cells[, grepl("CD", colnames(cells))] # A shortcut to get to the surface markers we care about
cells <- asinh(cells/5) %>% as_tibble()
cells <- cells[sample(nrow(cells), 4000),]
cells
library(umap)
library(Rtsne)

umap <- umap::umap(cells)$layout %>% as_tibble()
tsne <- Rtsne::Rtsne(X = cells)$Y %>% as_tibble()
setwd(here::here("output"))
Warning: The working directory was changed to /Users/tylerburns/Documents/projects/knn_sleepwalk/output inside a notebook chunk. The working directory will be reset when the chunk is finished running. Use the knitr root.dir option in the setup chunk to change the working directory for notebook chunks.
KnnSleepwalk(mat = cells, embedding = list(tsne, umap), k = 40, output_file = "knn_sleepwalk_cytof.html")
